Gospel singer Lynet Munyali, popularly known as Size 8 might just have committed the biggest fashion crime by donning faux leather fitting jeggings to the gym. Size 8 shared an Insta-Live while at a city gym on Monday evening. She was walking and jogging on the treadmill in faux jeggings and a fitting t-shirt. The mother of one however had proper gym shoes for her workout that was shared live on Instagram. Size 8's faux leather choice is a gym crime that people are often warned about. According to health experts, gym clothing should be free size and absorbent to ensure comfort and aeration during a workout. Designers have introduced semi faux leather leggings that have mesh sections for aeration while working out.